Phylogeny and review of the genus Alyssomyia Hull, with descriptions of two new species (Diptera, Asilidae, Stenopogoninae, Enigmomorphini)Abstract The robber fly genus Alyssomyia Hull was revised and two new species, A. frayleana n. sp. and A. limariensis n. sp. from the IV Region of Chile, are described and figured. A key to the seven known species of the genus is presented. A phylogenetic analysis using 23 characters revealed that Alyssomyia is monophyletic. A distribution map is presented for each species.